.. _addition_ref:

Addition
========

.. rst-class:: hidden

   This page describes the class :index:`Addition`

The algorithm used to add to arbitrary length numbers (``LongNum`` objects):

Input: ``N1``, ``N2``

I0: get the strings ``s1``, ``s2`` corresponding to the numbers and make them compatible by
   prepending or appending '0' digits.
    
   The position of the result's decimal point will be the larger of the decimal point positions of the two numbers.

I1: set the result to the empty string
